          <p id="OAS.IO.5">
      The ninth International Conference of American States (held in Bogotá, Colombia, in 1948) adopted the Charter of the Organization of American States, creating a successor to the Commercial Bureau of American Republics, founded in 1890, and the Pan-American Union. The OAS aims, 
      <i>inter alia,</i>
       to strengthen the peace and security of the continent; to promote human rights and consolidate representative democracy; to promote, through co-operative action, the economic, social and cultural development of member states; and to confront shared problems such as poverty, terrorism, the trade in illegal drugs, and corruption.
    </p>
