                    <endnote id="OAS.IO.18" ref-symbol="*">Cuba, a founding member, was suspended from OAS activities in 1962. The suspension was revoked by the OAS General Assembly in June 2009, although participation by Cuba in the organization was to be subject to further review.</endnote>
                    <endnote id="OAS.IO.18.2" ref-symbol="†">In April 2017 the Venezuelan regime headed by Nicolás Maduro Moros initiated a two-year process of withdrawal from the OAS. The OAS, however, denounced Maduro’s regime as illegitimate, and from 2019 until late 2022 recognized an opposition-led interim government. </endnote>
               </table-block-simple>
               <p>Note: Nicaragua formally withdrew from the organization in November 2023, having initiated a two-year process in November 2021 following condemnation by the OAS General Assembly of a general election that had been held in the country in that month.</p>
