     <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.95" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
          <heading>Organization</heading>
          <heading-note>April 2024</heading-note>
          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.96" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>General Assembly</heading>
               <p id="OAS.IO.43">The Assembly meets annually and may also hold special sessions when convoked by the Permanent Council. As the highest decision-making body of the OAS, it decides general action and policy. The 54th regular session of the Assembly was to be held in Asunción, Paraguay, in June 2024.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.97" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Meetings of Consultation of Ministers of Foreign Affairs</heading>
               <p id="OAS.IO.44">Meetings are convened, at the request of any member state, to consider problems of an urgent nature and of common interest to member states, or to serve as an organ of consultation in cases of armed attack or other threats to international peace and security. The Permanent Council determines whether a meeting should be convened and acts as a provisional organ of consultation until ministers are able to assemble.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.98" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Permanent Council</heading>
               <p>The Council, which meets regularly throughout the year, comprises representatives of each member state with the rank of ambassador. It has a General Committee and Committees on Juridical and Political Affairs, Hemispheric Security, Inter-American Summits Management and Civil Society Participation in OAS Activities, and Administrative and Budgetary Affairs. There are also ad hoc working groups. The Council guides ongoing policies and actions and oversees the maintenance of friendly relations between members. It supervises the work of the OAS and promotes co-operation with a variety of other international bodies, including the United Nations (UN). The chairmanship of the Council rotates on a three-monthly basis.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.100" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>General Secretariat</heading>
               <p id="OAS.IO.50">The General Secretariat performs the duties entrusted to it by the General Assembly, Meetings of Consultation of Ministers of Foreign Affairs and the Councils. The work of the General Secretariat is undertaken by separate Secretariats for Strengthening Democracy; Multidimensional Security; Hemispheric Affairs; Access to Rights and Equity; Legal Affairs; and Administration and Finance; and by the Executive Secretariat for Integral Development.</p>
               <p usage="edio sacac">There is an Administrative Tribunal, comprising six elected members, to settle staffing disputes. The Washington, DC-based Columbus Memorial Library holds official documentation and publications of the OAS. An OAS School of Governance, also located in Washington, DC, offers technical training and leadership development programmes for public, political and civic officials, and organizes research.</p>
