          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.99" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Inter-American Council for Integral Development (CIDI)</heading>
               <p>The Council, established in 1996, aims to promote co-operation among the countries of the region, in order to accelerate economic and social development. The Executive Secretariat for Integral Development provides CIDI with tech­nical and secretarial ser­vices, and co-ordinates a Special Multilateral Fund of CIDI (FEMCIDI). CIDI has three permanent committees, on Partnership for Development Policies; Migration Issues; and Programmes, Budget and Evaluation, and a working group tasked with preparing a draft Inter-American Business Charter. Technical co-operation and training programmes are managed by a subsidiary body of the Council, the Inter-American Agency for Co-operation and Development, which was established in 1999. Inter-American Committees (subsidiary organs of CIDI) cover: Culture; Education; Ports; Science and Technology; Social Development; Sustainable Development; and Tourism.</p>
