          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.99.2" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Inter-American Juridical Committee (CJI)</heading>
               <p id="OAS.IO.47.2">
        The Committee's purposes are to serve as an advisory body to the OAS on juridical matters; to promote the progressive development and codification of international law; and to study juridical problems relating to the integration of the developing countries in the hemisphere, and, in so far as may appear desirable, the possibility of attaining uniformity in legislation. It comprises 11 jurists, nationals of different member states, elected for a period of four years, with the possibility of re-election. In August 2023 the CJI adopted a 
        <publ-name>Guide to Best Practices in Jurisdictional Cooperation for the Americas</publ-name>
        .
      </p>
