          <int-org-section id="OAS.IO.54" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Inter-American Commission on Human Rights (IACHR)</heading>
               <p>The autonomous IACHR, established in 1960, promotes the observance and protection of human rights in member states. It is composed of seven members, elected for four-year terms. The Commission examines and reports on the human rights situation in member countries and considers individual petitions relating to alleged human rights violations by member states. Special Rapporteurs analyse and report on the rights of children; women; migrants; older persons; people with disabilities; indigenous peoples; Afro-descendants and racial discrimination; people deprived of liberty; lesbian, gay, trans, bisexual and intersex persons; prisoners; human rights defenders; economic, social, cultural and environmental rights; memory, truth and justice; and freedom of expression.</p>
